---
title: "Identifying brain regions supporting amygdalar functionality: Application of a novel graph theory technique"
collection: publications
category: manuscripts
excerpt: 'This paper applies a novel graph theory method to diffusion-based networks, finding that multiple, separable networks—not a single "amygdala network"—support different modes of amygdalar interaction with the larger brain network.'
date: 2021-12-01
venue: 'Neuroimage'
paperurl: 'https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34571162/'
citation: 'Matyi MA, Cioaba SM, Banich MT, Spielberg JM. (2021). &quot;Identifying brain regions supporting amygdalar functionality: Application of a novel graph theory technique.&quot; <i>Neuroimage</i>. 244:118614.'
